pageContext.claim: “As an example, when China makes a car, they sell it into the United States. There's 2 1/2 percent tariff, of which they don't pay. So they paid nothing. Other than that, it's a wonderful deal. When we make a car, we sell it into China, and there's a 25% tariff. And that's just the beginning, here's others. ”
pageContext.analysis: China lowered its 25 percent tariff on cars to 15 percent as of July 1. General Motors sells more cars in China (3.9 million) than in the US (3 million) and saw its China business grow 13 percent in 2016.
